summary:
****Sneak Peek at Chapter 18 of Winter Storm**** “And just what do you think you’re doing?”
Arya demanded in her best imitation...
caption:
****Sneak Peek at Chapter 18 of Winter Storm****

“And just what do you think you’re doing?” Arya demanded in her best imitation of Mother’s voice.

Sansa uttered a soft shriek of surprise, dropping the lemon cake that she’d been in the process of lifting to her mouth and spinning toward her, eyes wide with terror. Arya began to giggle just a little bit when Sansa clutched her chest like she’d had a horrid fright, her breath uneven and her expression one of terror before she recognised Arya.

“Oh, Arya!” Sansa shouted, swatting her in annoyance. “You scared me half to death!”

Arya laughed all the more.

“That was the point, Sansa,” Arya said. “Cook will be terribly cross with you when she wakes to find you’ve eaten all her lemon cakes before Aunt Lyanna can arrive.”

“I got hungry,” Sansa admitting, blushing prettily and lowering her head in shame, her hands cradling her pregnant belly.

Catch up here: https://www.fanfiction.net/s/11139862/1/Winter-Storm

title: Whump compilation: Game of Thrones
body:
This is a comprehensive list of whump in Game of Thrones.

 List established as of 8x06, series complete as of 2019.

Characters

Jamie Lannister (Nikolaj Coster-Waldau)

1x10, “Fire and Blood”, captured, tied-up, caged, blood

2x01, “The North Remembers”, bloddied, imprisoned

2x07, “A Man without Honor”, caged, collared, imprisoned

2x08, “The Prince of Winterfell”, manhandled

3x03, “Walk of Punishment”, tied-up, hand cut off

3x04, “And Now his Watch has Ended”, beaten, imprisoned

3x05, “Kissed by Fire”, stump cauterized, care

7x04, “The Spoils of War”, knocked off his horse, nearly drowns

7x05, “Eastwatch”, rescued from drowning, coughs up water, heavy breathing, angst, Cersei emotionaly manipulates him

8x05, “The Bells”, prisoner, collared, chained up, tied to a pole, rescued, fight, beaten up, stabbed in the side twice, burried under rubble, implied death

Jon Snow (Kit Harrington) 

1x03, “Lord Snow”, roughed up, knife to the throat

1x08, “The Pointy End”, burns his hand during a fight with a “zombie”

2x03, “What is Dead may never Die”, bloodied

3x10, “Mysha”, shot with an arrow

4x05, “First of His Name”, stabbed

4x09, “Watchers on the Wall”, battle, beaten up, grief

5x08, “Hardhome”, beaten-up

5x10, “Mother’s Mercy”, stabbed mutiple times in the chest

6x09, “The Battle of the Bastards”, battle, covered in blood

7x06, “Beyond the Wall”, falls into icy water, frozen/hypothermia, tended to

7x07, “The Dragon and the Wolf”, bedridden, tended to

8x03, “The Long Night”, battle, fight, blood

8x06, “The Iron Throne”, has to murder his romantic partner, grief, tears, exiled

Eddard Stark (Sean Bean)

1x05, “The Wolf and the Lion”, spear to the leg

1x06, “A Golden Crown”, recovery, feverish

1x07, “You Win or You Die”, hobbles around with a cane

1x08, “The Pointy End”, locked in a dungeon

Theon Greyjoy (Alfie Allen)

3x02, “Dark Wings, Dark Words”, tortured

3x03, “Walk of Punishment”, recaptured

3x06, “The Climb” , tortured, bound

3x10, “Mysha”, tortured, psychological torture

4x06, “The Laws of Gods and Men”, psychological torture

4x08, “The Mountain and the Viper”, psychological torture, forced betrayal

5x06, “Unbowed, Unbent, Unbroken”, angst, tears

7x02, “Stormborn”, fear, PTSD (?)

7x07, “The Dragon and the Wolf”, beaten up

8x03, “The Long Night”, battle, fight, blood, death

Jorah Mormont (Iain Glen)

5x05, “Kill the Boy”, angst

7x02, “Stormborn”, skin infection

8x03, “The Long Night”, battle, fight, blood, death

Khal Drogo (Jason Momoa)

1x08, “The Pointy End”, mortally wounded during a fight

1x09, “Baelor”, sick, sweaty, infection, feverish

Gendry Waters (Joe Dempsey)

3x08, “Second Sons”, tortured with leeches, tied up

Robb Stark (Richard Madden)

3x09, “The Rains of Castamere”, stabbed, death

Sandor Clegane (Rory McCann)

4x07, “Mockingbord”, wound on the shoulder

4x10, “The Children”, beaten, thrown off a cliff, left to die

Loras Tyrell (Finn Jones)

5x04, “The Sons of the Harpy”, marks carved on forehead

Edmure Tully (Tobias Menzies)

6x08, “No One”, used as a bargaining chip
